The paper discusses an optimization algorithm for deep neural network learning problems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The algorithm is specifically designed for convolutional neural network optimization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of adaptive learning rate, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the combination of ADAM and genetic algorithm suggests a potential application in control systems (cs.SY).
